Integrating the above expression  first with respect to $\alpha_3$ and subsequently with respect to $\alpha_2$, gives

\begin{eqnarray}
F_{2}(0)&=&\frac{\alpha}{\pi} \int^{1}_{0} dz \int^{1-z}_{0}dy \,\, \frac{z^{2}}{(1-z)\left[z+(1-z)^{2}\frac{m^{2}}{M^{2}}\right]}\nonumber\\
&=&\frac{\alpha}{\pi}\int^{1}_{0}dz \, \, \frac{z^{2}}{z+(1-z)^{2}\frac{m^{2}}{M^{2}}} \; .
\end{eqnarray}


Computing $F_{2}(0)$, we arrive at the conclusion that

\begin{eqnarray}\label{amm}
F_{2}(0)\!\!&\approx&\!\!\frac{\alpha}{2\pi}\left\lbrace1-\frac{2}{3}\left(\frac{m}{M}\right)^2 - 2\left[\frac{25}{12}+\ln\left(\frac{m}{M}\right) \right]\left(\frac{m}{M}\right)^4+\right.\nonumber\\
&&\left.{\cal O}\left[\left(\frac{m}{M}\right)^6\right]\right\rbrace.
\end{eqnarray}

